the long and winding road the fcc paves the path with good intentions siepr siepr stanford institute for economic policy research search the site enter your keywords main links home about siepr research at siepr education at siepr events at siepr people at siepr publications at siepr economics in the news support siepr contact us stay connected stay connected banner home publications profile display the long and winding road the fcc paves the path with good intentions type siepr discussion paper 01 008 author s gregory rosston published 12 1 01 download pdf abstract this papers shows through several case studies that the federal communications commission is having a difficult time moving toward more reliance on market forces the case studies highlight the problems with a case by case approach to spectrum management rather than a wholesale change in policy then the paper proposes a concrete method for moving toward much more market oriented spectrum policy it proposes a method of nomination and grant of additional flexibility and then a free entry system without barriers to entry the gains in consumer welfare from such a move could be substantial stanford university economics department stanford center for international development public policy program site map economic summit
